race.comment: This is tough. SAMURAI (6) resumes for the sharp Matt Dale yard and his best form stacks right up. Just missed over 1550m in a 72 at Canterbury two back and has placed 2/3 this trip. Draws out, but Heywood is reunited and count on him to manage. The betting will be key. ZIELLE (8) has the ability and looked a run short resuming here over shorter. Has come off a 64 win at Newcastle over 1400m and that form reads well. She will give away a start but hit the line hard. RILEYCAT (11) sits at the bottom of the handicap and can't be taken lightly. Went well three back in town and was only beaten 1.4L this grade last time at the Sapphire Coast. Draws inside and Collett is a key jockey engagement replacing the apprentice. CRIMSON MISS (9) has been freshened and would be in the finish at best. In good hands and keep onside.
